robots.txt is a simple text file placed in the root directory of a website (e.g., www.example.com/robots.txt). 
It is not strictly enforceable, a rogue bot could still ignore it.
Some websites intentionally include "honeypot" directories in robots.txt to lure malicious bots. Identifying such traps can provide insights into the target's security awareness and defensive measures.


